[[uid=830lwb1f]] proposing to Gwendolen, may I dine with
[[uid=830lwb1g]] you to-night at Willis’s?
[[uid=830lwb1h]] 
[[uid=830lwb1j]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwb1k]] I suppose so, if you want to.
[[uid=830lwb1l]] 
[[uid=830lwb1m]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb1n]] Yes, but you must be serious about it.
[[uid=830lwb1p]] I hate people who are not serious about [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb1q]] meals. It is so shallow of them.
[[uid=830lwb1r]] 
[[uid=830lwb1s]] [Enter Lane.]
[[uid=830lwb1t]] 
[[uid=830lwb1w]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwb1x]] Lady Bracknell and Miss Fairfax.
[[uid=830lwb1y]] 
[[uid=830lwb1z]] [Algernon goes forward to meet them.
[[uid=830lwb20]] Enter Lady Bracknell and Gwendolen.]
[[uid=830lwb21]] 
[[uid=830lwb22]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwb23]] Good afternoon, dear Algernon, I hope
[[uid=830lwb24]] you are behaving very well.
[[uid=830lwb25]] 
[[uid=830lwb26]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb27]] I’m feeling very well, Aunt Augusta.
[[uid=830lwb28]] 
[[uid=830lwb29]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwb2b]] That’s not quite the same thing. In
[[uid=830lwb2c]] fact the two things rarely go together.
[[uid=830lwb2d]] [Sees Jack and bows to him with icy
[[uid=830lwb2f]] coldness.]
[[uid=830lwb2g]] 
[[uid=830lwb2h]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb2j]] [To Gwendolen.] Dear me, you are smart!
[[uid=830lwb2k]] 
[[uid=830lwb2l]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwb2m]] I am always smart! Am I not, Mr.
[[uid=830lwb2n]] Worthing?
[[uid=830lwb2p]] 
[[uid=830lwb2q]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwb2r]] You’re quite perfect, Miss Fairfax.
[[uid=830lwb2s]] 
[[uid=830lwb2t]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwb2w]] Oh! I hope I am not that. It would
[[uid=830lwb2x]] leave no room for developments, and I
[[uid=830lwb2y]] intend to develop in many directions.
[[uid=830lwb2z]] [Gwendolen and Jack sit down together [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwb30]] in the corner.]
[[uid=830lwb31]] 
[[uid=830lwb32]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwb33]] I’m sorry if we are a little late,
[[uid=830lwb34]] Algernon, but I was obliged to call on
[[uid=830lwb35]] dear Lady Harbury. I hadn’t been there [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb36]] since her poor husband’s death. I never
[[uid=830lwb37]] saw a woman so altered; she looks quite [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb38]] twenty years younger. And now I’ll have
