[[uid=830lwb3b]] cucumber sandwiches you promised me.
[[uid=830lwb3c]] 
[[uid=830lwb3d]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb3f]] Certainly, Aunt Augusta. [Goes over to
[[uid=830lwb3g]] tea-table.]
[[uid=830lwb3h]] 
[[uid=830lwb3j]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwb3k]] Won’t you come and sit here, Gwendolen?
[[uid=830lwb3l]] 
[[uid=830lwb3m]] GWENDOLEN. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb3n]] Thanks, mamma, I’m quite comfortable
[[uid=830lwb3p]] where I am.
[[uid=830lwb3q]] 
[[uid=830lwb3r]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb3s]] [Picking up empty plate in horror.]
[[uid=830lwb3t]] Good heavens! Lane! Why are there no
[[uid=830lwb3w]] cucumber sandwiches? I ordered them
[[uid=830lwb3x]] specially.
[[uid=830lwb3y]] 
[[uid=830lwb3z]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwb40]] [Gravely.] There were no cucumbers in
