[[uid=830lwb42]] down twice.
[[uid=830lwb43]]  [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb44]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb45]] No cucumbers!
[[uid=830lwb46]] 
[[uid=830lwb47]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwb48]] No, sir. Not even for ready money.
[[uid=830lwb49]] 
[[uid=830lwb4b]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb4c]] That will do, Lane, thank you.
[[uid=830lwb4d]] 
[[uid=830lwb4f]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwb4g]] Thank you, sir. [Goes out.]
[[uid=830lwb4h]] 
[[uid=830lwb4j]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb4k]] I am greatly distressed, Aunt Augusta,
[[uid=830lwb4l]] about there being no cucumbers, not
[[uid=830lwb4m]] even for ready money.
[[uid=830lwb4n]] 
[[uid=830lwb4p]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwb4q]] It really makes no matter, Algernon. I
[[uid=830lwb4r]] had some crumpets with Lady Harbury,
[[uid=830lwb4s]] who seems to me to be living entirely
[[uid=830lwb4t]] for pleasure now.
[[uid=830lwb4w]] 
[[uid=830lwb4x]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwb4y]] I hear her hair has turned quite gold
[[uid=830lwb4z]] from grief.
[[uid=830lwb50]] 
[[uid=830lwb51]] LADY BRACKNELL.
[[uid=830lwb52]] It certainly has changed its colour.
[[uid=830lwb53]] From what cause I, of course, cannot
[[uid=830lwb54]] say. [Algernon crosses and hands tea.]
[[uid=830lwb55]] Thank you. I’ve quite a treat for you
[[uid=830lwb56]] to-night, Algernon. I am going to send
