[[uid=830lwb6z]] I rely on you to arrange my music for
[[uid=830lwb70]] me. It is my last reception, and one
[[uid=830lwb71]] wants something that will encourage [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwb72]] conversation, particularly at the end
[[uid=830lwb73]] of the season when every one has
[[uid=830lwb74]] practically said whatever they had to
[[uid=830lwb75]] say, which, in most cases, was probably [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb76]] not much.
[[uid=830lwb77]] 
[[uid=830lwb78]] ALGERNON. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwb79]] I’ll speak to Bunbury, Aunt Augusta, if
