[[uid=830lwbw3]] your own aunt in that way before you.
[[uid=830lwbw4]] 
[[uid=830lwbw5]] ALGERNON. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwbw6]] My dear boy, I love hearing my
[[uid=830lwbw7]] relations abused. It is the only thing
[[uid=830lwbw8]] that makes me put up with them at all.
[[uid=830lwbw9]] Relations are simply a tedious pack of
[[uid=830lwbwb]] people, who haven’t got the remotest
[[uid=830lwbwc]] knowledge of how to live, nor the
[[uid=830lwbwd]] smallest instinct about when to die.
[[uid=830lwbwf]] 
[[uid=830lwbwg]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbwh]] Oh, that is nonsense!
[[uid=830lwbwj]] 
[[uid=830lwbwk]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbwl]] It isn’t!
[[uid=830lwbwm]] 
[[uid=830lwbwn]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbwp]] Well, I won’t argue about the matter. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwbwq]] You always want to argue about things.
[[uid=830lwbwr]] 
[[uid=830lwbws]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbwt]] That is exactly what things were
[[uid=830lwbww]] originally made for.
[[uid=830lwbwx]] 
[[uid=830lwbwy]] JACK. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwbwz]] Upon my word, if I thought that, I’d
[[uid=830lwbx0]] shoot myself . . . [A pause.] You don’t
[[uid=830lwbx1]] think there is any chance of Gwendolen
[[uid=830lwbx2]] becoming like her mother in about a
[[uid=830lwbx3]] hundred and fifty years, do you, Algy? [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwbx4]] 
[[uid=830lwbx5]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbx6]] All women become like their mothers. [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwbx7]] That is their tragedy. No man does.
[[uid=830lwbx8]] That’s his.
[[uid=830lwbx9]] 
[[uid=830lwbxb]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbxc]] Is that clever?
[[uid=830lwbxd]] 
[[uid=830lwbxf]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbxg]] It is perfectly phrased! and quite as
[[uid=830lwbxh]] true as any observation in civilised
[[uid=830lwbxj]] life should be.
[[uid=830lwbxk]] 
[[uid=830lwbxl]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbxm]] I am sick to death of cleverness.
[[uid=830lwbxn]] Everybody is clever nowadays. You can’t
[[uid=830lwbxp]] go anywhere without meeting clever
[[uid=830lwbxq]] people. The thing has become an
[[uid=830lwbxr]] absolute public nuisance. I wish to
[[uid=830lwbxs]] goodness we had a few fools left.
[[uid=830lwbxt]] 
[[uid=830lwbxw]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbxx]] We have.
[[uid=830lwbxy]] 
[[uid=830lwbxz]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwby0]] I should extremely like to meet them.
[[uid=830lwby1]] What do they talk about? [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwby2]] 
[[uid=830lwby3]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwby4]] The fools? Oh! about the clever people, [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwby5]] of course.
[[uid=830lwby6]] 
[[uid=830lwby7]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwby8]] What fools!
[[uid=830lwby9]] 
[[uid=830lwbyb]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbyc]] By the way, did you tell Gwendolen the
[[uid=830lwbyd]] truth about your being Ernest in town,
[[uid=830lwbyf]] and Jack in the country?
[[uid=830lwbyg]] 
[[uid=830lwbyh]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbyj]] [In a very patronising manner.] My dear
[[uid=830lwbyk]] fellow, the truth isn’t quite the sort
[[uid=830lwbyl]] of thing one tells to a nice, sweet,
[[uid=830lwbym]] refined girl. What extraordinary ideas
[[uid=830lwbyn]] you have about the way to behave to a
[[uid=830lwbyp]] woman!
[[uid=830lwbyq]] 
[[uid=830lwbyr]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbys]] The only way to behave to a woman is to
[[uid=830lwbyt]] make love to her, if she is pretty, and
[[uid=830lwbyw]] to some one else, if she is plain.
[[uid=830lwbyx]] 
[[uid=830lwbyy]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbyz]] Oh, that is nonsense.
[[uid=830lwbz0]] 
[[uid=830lwbz1]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbz2]] What about your brother? What about the
[[uid=830lwbz3]] profligate Ernest?
[[uid=830lwbz4]] 
[[uid=830lwbz5]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbz6]] Oh, before the end of the week I shall
[[uid=830lwbz7]] have got rid of him. I’ll say he died
[[uid=830lwbz8]] in Paris of apoplexy. Lots of people
[[uid=830lwbz9]] die of apoplexy, quite suddenly, don’t
[[uid=830lwbzb]] they?
[[uid=830lwbzc]] 
[[uid=830lwbzd]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbzf]] Yes, but it’s hereditary, my dear
[[uid=830lwbzg]] fellow. It’s a sort of thing that runs
[[uid=830lwbzh]] in families. You had much better say a
[[uid=830lwbzj]] severe chill.
[[uid=830lwbzk]] 
[[uid=830lwbzl]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbzm]] You are sure a severe chill isn’t
[[uid=830lwbzn]] hereditary, or anything of that kind?
[[uid=830lwbzp]] 
[[uid=830lwbzq]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwbzr]] Of course it isn’t!
[[uid=830lwbzs]] 
[[uid=830lwbzt]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwbzw]] Very well, then. My poor brother Ernest
[[uid=830lwbzx]] is carried off suddenly, in Paris, by a
[[uid=830lwbzy]] severe chill. That gets rid of him.
[[uid=830lwbzz]] 
[[uid=830lwc00]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc01]] But I thought you said that . . . Miss
[[uid=830lwc02]] Cardew was a little too much interested
[[uid=830lwc03]] in your poor brother Ernest? Won’t she
[[uid=830lwc04]] feel his loss a good deal?
[[uid=830lwc05]] 
[[uid=830lwc06]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc07]] Oh, that is all right. Cecily is not a
[[uid=830lwc08]] silly romantic girl, I am glad to say.
[[uid=830lwc09]] She has got a capital appetite, goes
[[uid=830lwc0b]] long walks, and pays no attention at
[[uid=830lwc0c]] all to her lessons.
[[uid=830lwc0d]] 
[[uid=830lwc0f]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc0g]] I would rather like to see Cecily.
[[uid=830lwc0h]] 
[[uid=830lwc0j]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc0k]] I will take very good care you never
[[uid=830lwc0l]] do. She is excessively pretty, and she
[[uid=830lwc0m]] is only just eighteen.
[[uid=830lwc0n]] 
[[uid=830lwc0p]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc0q]] Have you told Gwendolen yet that you
[[uid=830lwc0r]] have an excessively pretty ward who is
[[uid=830lwc0s]] only just eighteen?
[[uid=830lwc0t]] 
[[uid=830lwc0w]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc0x]] Oh! one doesn’t blurt these things out
[[uid=830lwc0y]] to people. Cecily and Gwendolen are
[[uid=830lwc0z]] perfectly certain to be extremely great
[[uid=830lwc10]] friends. I’ll bet you anything you like
[[uid=830lwc11]] that half an hour after they have met,
[[uid=830lwc12]] they will be calling each other sister. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwc13]] 
[[uid=830lwc14]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc15]] Women only do that when they have
[[uid=830lwc16]] called each other a lot of other things
[[uid=830lwc17]] first. Now, my dear boy, if we want to
[[uid=830lwc18]] get a good table at Willis’s, we really
[[uid=830lwc19]] must go and dress. Do you know it is
[[uid=830lwc1b]] nearly seven?
[[uid=830lwc1c]] 
[[uid=830lwc1d]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc1f]] [Irritably.] Oh! It always is nearly
[[uid=830lwc1g]] seven.
[[uid=830lwc1h]] 
[[uid=830lwc1j]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc1k]] Well, I’m hungry.
[[uid=830lwc1l]] 
[[uid=830lwc1m]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc1n]] I never knew you when you weren’t . . .
[[uid=830lwc1p]] 
[[uid=830lwc1q]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc1r]] What shall we do after dinner? Go to a
[[uid=830lwc1s]] theatre?
[[uid=830lwc1t]] 
[[uid=830lwc1w]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc1x]] Oh no! I loathe listening.
[[uid=830lwc1y]] 
[[uid=830lwc1z]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc20]] Well, let us go to the Club?
[[uid=830lwc21]] 
[[uid=830lwc22]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc23]] Oh, no! I hate talking.
[[uid=830lwc24]] 
[[uid=830lwc25]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc26]] Well, we might trot round to the Empire
[[uid=830lwc27]] at ten?
[[uid=830lwc28]] 
[[uid=830lwc29]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc2b]] Oh, no! I can’t bear looking at things.
[[uid=830lwc2c]] It is so silly. [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwc2d]] 
[[uid=830lwc2f]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc2g]] Well, what shall we do?
[[uid=830lwc2h]] 
[[uid=830lwc2j]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc2k]] Nothing!
[[uid=830lwc2l]] 
[[uid=830lwc2m]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc2n]] It is awfully hard work doing nothing.
[[uid=830lwc2p]] However, I don’t mind hard work where
[[uid=830lwc2q]] there is no definite object of any [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwc2r]] kind. [[attitudeInstr]] [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwc2s]] 
[[uid=830lwc2t]] [Enter Lane.] [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwc2w]] 
[[uid=830lwc2x]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc2y]] Miss Fairfax.
[[uid=830lwc2z]] 
[[uid=830lwc30]] [Enter Gwendolen. Lane goes out.]
[[uid=830lwc31]] 
[[uid=830lwc32]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc33]] Gwendolen, upon my word!
[[uid=830lwc34]] 
[[uid=830lwc35]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc36]] Algy, kindly turn your back. I have
[[uid=830lwc37]] something very particular to say to Mr.
[[uid=830lwc38]] Worthing.
[[uid=830lwc39]] 
[[uid=830lwc3b]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc3c]] Really, Gwendolen, I don’t think I can
[[uid=830lwc3d]] allow this at all.
[[uid=830lwc3f]] 
[[uid=830lwc3g]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc3h]] Algy, you always adopt a strictly
[[uid=830lwc3j]] immoral attitude towards life. You are
[[uid=830lwc3k]] not quite old enough to do that.
[[uid=830lwc3l]] [Algernon retires to the fireplace.]
[[uid=830lwc3m]] 
[[uid=830lwc3n]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc3p]] My own darling!
[[uid=830lwc3q]] 
[[uid=830lwc3r]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc3s]] Ernest, we may never be married. From
[[uid=830lwc3t]] the expression on mamma’s face I fear
[[uid=830lwc3w]] we never shall. Few parents nowadays
[[uid=830lwc3x]] pay any regard to what their children
[[uid=830lwc3y]] say to them. The old-fashioned respect
[[uid=830lwc3z]] for the young is fast dying out.
[[uid=830lwc40]] Whatever influence I ever had over
[[uid=830lwc41]] mamma, I lost at the age of three. But
[[uid=830lwc42]] although she may prevent us from
[[uid=830lwc43]] becoming man and wife, and I may marry
[[uid=830lwc44]] some one else, and marry often, nothing
[[uid=830lwc45]] that she can possibly do can alter my
[[uid=830lwc46]] eternal devotion to you.
[[uid=830lwc47]]  [[attitudeInstr]]
[[uid=830lwc48]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc49]] Dear Gwendolen!
[[uid=830lwc4b]] 
[[uid=830lwc4c]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc4d]] The story of your romantic origin, as
[[uid=830lwc4f]] related to me by mamma, with unpleasing
[[uid=830lwc4g]] comments, has naturally stirred the
[[uid=830lwc4h]] deeper fibres of my nature. Your
[[uid=830lwc4j]] Christian name has an irresistible
[[uid=830lwc4k]] fascination. The simplicity of your
[[uid=830lwc4l]] character makes you exquisitely
[[uid=830lwc4m]] incomprehensible to me. Your town
[[uid=830lwc4n]] address at the Albany I have. What is
[[uid=830lwc4p]] your address in the country?
[[uid=830lwc4q]] 
[[uid=830lwc4r]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc4s]] The Manor House, Woolton, [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwc4t]] Hertfordshire.
[[uid=830lwc4w]] 
[[uid=830lwc4x]] [Algernon, who has been carefully
[[uid=830lwc4y]] listening, smiles to himself, and
[[uid=830lwc4z]] writes the address on his shirt-cuff.
[[uid=830lwc50]] Then picks up the Railway Guide.]
[[uid=830lwc51]] 
[[uid=830lwc52]] GWENDOLEN. [[attitudeExp]]
[[uid=830lwc53]] There is a good postal service, I
[[uid=830lwc54]] suppose? It may be necessary to do
[[uid=830lwc55]] something desperate. That of course
[[uid=830lwc56]] will require serious consideration. I
[[uid=830lwc57]] will communicate with you daily.
[[uid=830lwc58]] 
[[uid=830lwc59]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc5b]] My own one!
[[uid=830lwc5c]] 
[[uid=830lwc5d]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc5f]] How long do you remain in town?
[[uid=830lwc5g]] 
[[uid=830lwc5h]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc5j]] Till Monday.
[[uid=830lwc5k]] 
[[uid=830lwc5l]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc5m]] Good! Algy, you may turn round now.
[[uid=830lwc5n]] 
[[uid=830lwc5p]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc5q]] Thanks, I’ve turned round already.
[[uid=830lwc5r]] 
[[uid=830lwc5s]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc5t]] You may also ring the bell.
[[uid=830lwc5w]] 
[[uid=830lwc5x]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc5y]] You will let me see you to your
[[uid=830lwc5z]] carriage, my own darling?
[[uid=830lwc60]] 
[[uid=830lwc61]] GWENDOLEN.
[[uid=830lwc62]] Certainly.
[[uid=830lwc63]] 
[[uid=830lwc64]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc65]] [To Lane, who now enters.] I will see
[[uid=830lwc66]] Miss Fairfax out.
[[uid=830lwc67]] 
[[uid=830lwc68]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc69]] Yes, sir. [Jack and Gwendolen go off.]
[[uid=830lwc6b]] 
[[uid=830lwc6c]] [Lane presents several letters on a
[[uid=830lwc6d]] salver to Algernon. It is to be
[[uid=830lwc6f]] surmised that they are bills, as
[[uid=830lwc6g]] Algernon, after looking at the
[[uid=830lwc6h]] envelopes, tears them up.]
[[uid=830lwc6j]] 
[[uid=830lwc6k]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc6l]] A glass of sherry, Lane.
[[uid=830lwc6m]] 
[[uid=830lwc6n]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc6p]] Yes, sir.
[[uid=830lwc6q]] 
[[uid=830lwc6r]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc6s]] To-morrow, Lane, I’m going Bunburying.
[[uid=830lwc6t]] 
[[uid=830lwc6w]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc6x]] Yes, sir.
[[uid=830lwc6y]] 
[[uid=830lwc6z]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc70]] I shall probably not be back till
[[uid=830lwc71]] Monday. You can put up my dress
[[uid=830lwc72]] clothes, my smoking jacket, and all the
[[uid=830lwc73]] Bunbury suits . . .
[[uid=830lwc74]] 
[[uid=830lwc75]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc76]] Yes, sir. [Handing sherry.]
[[uid=830lwc77]] 
[[uid=830lwc78]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc79]] I hope to-morrow will be a fine day,
[[uid=830lwc7b]] Lane.
[[uid=830lwc7c]] 
[[uid=830lwc7d]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc7f]] It never is, sir.
[[uid=830lwc7g]] 
[[uid=830lwc7h]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc7j]] Lane, you’re a perfect pessimist.
[[uid=830lwc7k]] 
[[uid=830lwc7l]] LANE.
[[uid=830lwc7m]] I do my best to give satisfaction, sir.
[[uid=830lwc7n]] 
[[uid=830lwc7p]] [Enter Jack. Lane goes off.]
[[uid=830lwc7q]] 
[[uid=830lwc7r]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc7s]] There’s a sensible, intellectual girl!
[[uid=830lwc7t]] the only girl I ever cared for in my
[[uid=830lwc7w]] life. [Algernon is laughing
[[uid=830lwc7x]] immoderately.] What on earth are you so
[[uid=830lwc7y]] amused at?
[[uid=830lwc7z]] 
[[uid=830lwc80]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc81]] Oh, I’m a little anxious about poor
[[uid=830lwc82]] Bunbury, that is all.
[[uid=830lwc83]] 
[[uid=830lwc84]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc85]] If you don’t take care, your friend
[[uid=830lwc86]] Bunbury will get you into a serious
[[uid=830lwc87]] scrape some day.
[[uid=830lwc88]] 
[[uid=830lwc89]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc8b]] I love scrapes. They are the only
[[uid=830lwc8c]] things that are never serious.
[[uid=830lwc8d]] 
[[uid=830lwc8f]] JACK.
[[uid=830lwc8g]] Oh, that’s nonsense, Algy. You never
[[uid=830lwc8h]] talk anything but nonsense.
[[uid=830lwc8j]] 
[[uid=830lwc8k]] ALGERNON.
[[uid=830lwc8l]] Nobody ever does.
[[uid=830lwc8m]] 
[[uid=830lwc8n]] [Jack looks indignantly at him, and
[[uid=830lwc8p]] leaves the room. Algernon lights a
[[uid=830lwc8q]] cigarette, reads his shirt-cuff, and
[[uid=830lwc8r]] smiles.]
[[uid=830lwc8s]] 
[[uid=830lwc8t]] ACT DROP
